We want to make tools, processes, and communities that develop technology inclusive, along every dimension of identity. Learn more about the vision and prime directive of the GitHub accessibility program in this blog post.

GitHub, accessibility, and the disability divide | The GitHub Blog
We just published our vision for GitHub accessibility at accessibility.github.com. Here’s the TL;DR: the prime directive of the GitHub accessibility program is to empower people with disabilities to build cool technology.
